            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;FACULTY OF MEDICINE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;SENIOR LECTURER IN PAEDIATRICS AND ADOLESCENT HEALTH&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO. FM/PAH 1/2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidates will: &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;teach undergraduate medical students and postgraduate students; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(ii)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;conduct research and/or creative professional works in his/her areas of expertise and supervise undergraduate and postgraduate students’ research projects&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(iii)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;provide clinical care in affiliated hospitals; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(iv)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;carry out any other duties as assigned by the head of the department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Candidates should have: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;(i) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;at least a Bachelor of Medicine/Bachelor of Surgery or other recognized Medical doctor qualification (MD); &lt;strong&gt;(ii) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;a specialist qualification in General Paediatrics or Paediatric Sub-Specialty; &lt;strong&gt;(iii) &lt;/strong&gt;the qualification must be registerable by the Botswana Health Professions Council with a specialist status; &lt;strong&gt;(iv)&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;evidence of governance and social engagement; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;(v)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; minimum of &lt;strong&gt;6&lt;/strong&gt; pieces of research products (e.g. articles, book chapters, peer reviewed conference proceedings) published by recognized publishers, &lt;strong&gt;3&lt;/strong&gt; of which must be articles in refereed/accredited journals in internationally recognized indexing databases; &lt;strong&gt;(vi)&lt;/strong&gt; paper/poster presentation at national and/or international conferences, depending on the discipline; &lt;strong&gt;(vii)&lt;/strong&gt; be lead and /or last author in at least (2 of 3) refereed journal publications; &lt;strong&gt;(viii)&lt;/strong&gt; publications should be spread nationally and/or internationally and across journals; &lt;strong&gt;(ix)&lt;/strong&gt; some research impact, including but not limited to citations, the h-index, patents, policy applications, peer reviews, publications that are prescribed in texts in other institutions etc (required in at least 1 of these); &lt;strong&gt;(x)&lt;/strong&gt; recognized as being of at least national research or effective clinical professional standing (e.g reviewer for refereed/ accredited national and regional publishers, editorial board member of at least national publisher in a relevant field, invitation as keynote speaker at national and international conferences/symposia (required in at least 1 of these); &lt;strong&gt;(xi)&lt;/strong&gt; active maintenance of a licence to practice issued by a the relevant professional licensing authority; successful supervision/co-supervision of research projects/post-doctoral/clinical research fellow supervision; &lt;strong&gt;(xii)&lt;/strong&gt; sustained professional research output; a minimum of 1 peer reviewed publications every 2 years&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;or 2 new Creative Professional Work every 6 years or since last promotion shall constitute sustained research output. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The following will be added advantages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; sustained research activity; on-going internally and externally-funded research activity; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; research/clinical effectiveness awards and other forms research recognition; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; examiner for undergraduate and/or postgraduate projects nationally. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Attributes and skills required (i) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent communication and organizational skills: &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; Strong academic leadership skills and sympathy for the values and culture of the University &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; Good management, human relations and sound analytical and coordinating skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The curriculum vitae (CV) should contain a detailed list of publications; clearly specifying titles of publications, dates published, name(s) of publishers and name(s) of co-authors if any. Publications should be categorized into: books, monographs, refereed and non-refereed journals, chapters in books, etc.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; The University offers competitive salaries and benefits commensurate with experience and qualifications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;How to apply:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Applicants are to address the stated qualification and provide other information to assist the university determine their suitability for the position.  They should provide current CV’s (including telephone and e-mail), certified copies of educational certificates and transcripts, and THREE (3) reference letters.  Applicants should inform their referees to:  (i) Quote the position applied for and (ii) submit their references directly to the address below:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Human Resources Manager, Faculty of Medicine, Corner of Notwane and Mabuto Road, University of Botswana, Private Bag 00713 Gaborone, Botswana; or Email to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:nkangana@.ub.ac.%20bw"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;nkangana@.ub.ac. bw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be sent to Faculty of Medicine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;, UB Teaching Hospital, 3rd Floor, Office F 4003&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;NB: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
